    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">How to make international calls?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            To make international calls from China, first dial "00" (international access code), then dial the target country's calling code (without the + sign), and finally dial the local phone number. For example, to call a US number: 00-1-local number.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Why do some countries have multiple calling codes?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Some large countries may have multiple calling codes, usually due to historical reasons or geographical divisions. Our database displays the main calling codes. Please refer to local carrier guidance for specific usage.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Is the time information accurate?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Our time information is obtained in real-time through authoritative time APIs, considering factors such as daylight saving time, with high accuracy. However, we recommend confirming the local time again before important calls.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Are the data sources reliable?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Our data comes from authoritative institutions such as the ITU International Telecommunication Union and is regularly updated. All information is for reference only. Please refer to the latest regulations of local carriers for actual use.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
